    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "(Read https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39006, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22313 before commenting here.)\n\n## Problem\n\nNvim can't load WASM treesitter parsers.\n\n## Proposal \n\nFind a \"lightweight c based runtime\" instead of the rust-based [wasmtime](https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime). It might be slower / less features than wasmtime, but that's ok as an initial step to unblock our \"treesitter parser distribution\" story. We can always reconsider wasmtime later.\n\nAlternatively, find a way to deliver wasmtime without making it a hard build-time dependency.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I would say make wasm support optional, but you will still require to add wasmtime for wasm support. There is not really a \"lightweight c based runtime\" since wasmtime is already minimal enough already. An example of this in action is in nix the package manager for wasm support: https://github.com/NixOS/nix/pull/15380",
            "created_at": "2026-04-14T11:50:24Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39008#issuecomment-4243636134",
