        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Not true; there's https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasm-micro-runtime. The issue is that tree-sitter uses wasmtime specifically for its C API, but that doesn't mean that other runtimes can't be used (today). Needs someone to investigate the gaps in its API and whether they can be filled.\n\nThe story may also change substantially once Zig matures, which 1. actually contains a (minimal) wasm runtime for bootstrapping and 2. opens the door for new projects (which I won't link here since they're not guaranteed to reach maturity).\n\n(And I have to remind people that we already have optional WASM support; all it takes is 1. someone to take ownership to make sure it still works after upstream changes and 2. allowing dynamic linking of wasmtime so we can punt to distros instead of tainting our own build process.)",
            "created_at": "2026-04-14T12:34:24Z",
